  "experimental_design_for_optimization": {
    "purpose": "To design a pulsatile formulation of lornoxicam to treat rheumatoid arthritis as per the chronotherapeutic pattern of the disease, targeting drug release in the early morning hours.",
    "approach": "Two-step process: 1) Preparation of fast-disintegrating core tablets with varying disintegrant (crospovidone) concentration. 2) Compression coating of the optimized core tablet with different ratios and combinations of hydrophobic (ethyl cellulose) and hydrophilic (HPMC K4M, L-hpc, NaCMC) polymers to achieve a lag time of ~5.5 hours.",
    "optimized_formulation": "F-5, which released lornoxicam after a lag time of 5.5 ± 0.7 hours and 99.81 ± 0.81% up to 8 hours."
  },
